Note = {21st International Conference on Artificial Intelligence Applications
   and Innovations-AIAI-Annual, Limassol, CYPRUS, JUN 26-29, 2025},
Abstract = {The evolution of Generative AI and AI Agents is continuously disrupting
   all fields of human-related activities, from daily life to enterprises
   and public sector. It is a common practice nowadays for all modern
   digital platforms to incorporate approaches which implement ChatBots
   using Large Language Models - LLMs to facilitate user interactivity,
   enrich the capabilities of the systems, and generally offer to the users
   an improved experience. Furthermore, in the field of healthcare,
   ChatBots and AI Agents are increasingly integrated into systems and
   applications for providing recommendations to the users, and interact
   with them to provide health and wellness-related information and respond
   to their questions. However, most of them use general-purpose LLMs, and
   therefore the respective results are not expected to be as accurate as
   required in the field of healthcare. Other approaches follow the method
   of fine-tuning to solve the limitation of inaccurate results but spend a
   lot of resources and time to achieve it. This work highlights the
   development of a novel Q\&A ChatBot enhanced by innovative techniques to
   achieve high-accuracy results in the field of Medical Information. The
   advantage of the proposed prototype is that it integrates easily with
   healthcare platforms, both under development or already existing, to
   provide information and insights about medicines and patients' drug
   treatment.},
